  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given Event Type "Meeting" is selected, when control updates, then Meeting's configuration
      (required fields, hidden fields) is fetched from Dataverse.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given Event Type is changed from "Meeting" to "Deadline", when control updates, then
      Deadline's configuration is fetched and replaces Meeting's.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given no Event Type is selected, when form loads, then control shows no configuration
      (waiting for selection).
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Control builds without TypeScript errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Event Type configuration format (expected from task 003):
    - Required fields: comma-separated field names
    - Hidden fields: comma-separated field names

    Example configuration for "Meeting":
    - Required: subject, scheduledstart, scheduledend, location
    - Hidden: reminderdate
